    <item>
      <title>SoftPos</title>
      <link>https://saftaja.com.sa/ar/softpos/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://saftaja.com.sa/ar/softpos/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure class=&#34;center-image&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://res.cloudinary.com/dgaxapjlp/image/upload/v1745391010/soft_pos_rvq6df.png&#34;&#xA;    alt=&#34;f360&#34; width=&#34;80%&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;!-- &#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://saftaja.com.sa/img/drone_ser/image1to2.png&#34;&#xA;    alt=&#34;Drone in Agriculture&#34; width=&#34;100%&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;## 1. Survey &amp; aerial Mapping&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;We offer precise survey and aerial mapping services using advanced UAV technology, enabling accurate topographic data collection, land use planning, and environmental monitoring with high-resolution imagery.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;In today’s rapidly evolving world, the demand for accurate and comprehensive mapping and surveying has never been greater. Aerial mapping technologies, powered by drones and advanced imaging techniques, have revolutionized the way we gather and analyze data for urban planning, infrastructure development, environmental assessments, and agricultural management. By capturing high-resolution images and precise geographical information, these technologies facilitate informed decision-making, enhance project efficiency, and promote sustainable development. This document explores the key applications of aerial mapping in urban planning, infrastructure, area profiling, and agricultural services.&#xD;&#xA;### i. Survey &amp; Aerial Mapping for Urban Planning&#xD;&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://saftaja.com.sa/img/drone_ser/image-urban.jpg&#34;&#xA;    alt=&#34;Urban Planning&#34; width=&#34;70%&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;Urban planning involves designing and organizing the physical, social, and economic aspects of cities. Aerial mapping plays a pivotal role in this process by providing detailed visual data that helps planners make informed decisions.&#xD;&#xA;* Cities/Buildings/Gardens: High-resolution aerial images allow planners to analyze land use patterns, identify potential growth areas, and assess the current state of urban infrastructure. This data can be used to create 3D models, visualize proposed developments, and enhance public engagement through interactive maps. Moreover, understanding the distribution of green spaces, such as parks and gardens, is vital for promoting biodiversity and improving residents&#39; quality of life. --&gt;</description>
    </item>
